.TH "bdx_probe" 9 "bdx_probe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bdx_probe \- Device Initialization Routine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bdx_probe
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct pci_device_id *ent "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device information struct
.IP "ent" 12
entry in bdx_pci_tbl
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, negative on failure

bdx_probe initializes an adapter identified by a pci_dev structure.
The OS initialization, configuring of the adapter private structure,
and a hardware reset occur.

functions and their order used as explained in
/usr/src/linux/Documentation/DMA-{API,mapping}.txt
